{{other people}} '''Benjamin T. Hudson''' is an [[United States|American]] [[Middle Ages|medievalist]] based at [[Pennsylvania State University]] in [[State College, Pennsylvania]]. He received his [[Bachelor of Arts]] degree at Pennsylvania State University, received his [[Master of Philosophy|Masters]] at [[University College, Dublin]], and his [[D.Phil.]] at [[Worcester College, Oxford]]. He specializes in the history of [[Celtic languages|Celtic-speaking]] peoples in the British Isles in the [[Early Middle Ages|Early]] and [[High Middle Ages]], and in the [[Norse-Gaelic]] [[Irish Sea]] region of the same period.
